=== NVIDIA GPU Memory Diagnostic Attempt ===
Date: 2026-03-31
GPU: NVIDIA GA104M RTX 3080 Laptop (10DE:249C, corrupted VBIOS)

Tools: MODS v367.38.1 (built from source with kernel 6.19 compat patches)
       MATS from same version

== MODS kernel module ==
Status: BUILT SUCCESSFULLY (mods.ko, 2.1MB)
Compat patches applied:
  - DEFINE_PCI_DEVICE_TABLE → static const struct pci_device_id
  - enum pci_channel_state → pci_channel_state_t
  - pci_map_page → dma_map_page (with &dev->dev fix)
  - ioremap_nocache → ioremap  
  - ACPI functions stubbed (not needed for memory test)

== MATS ==
Result: "Error: Unable to open /dev/mods" (when mods.ko already in use)
        OR: No output at all (version 367 may not recognize GA104)

== MODS ==  
Result: "Please unload the 'nouveau' kernel module!"
Root cause: Stock nouveau auto-loads from initramfs and can't be unloaded
            (has 1 user despite failing to initialize GPU)

== Limitations ==
1. Version 367.38.1 only supports GP10x (Pascal) — does NOT have GA104 (Ampere) support
   - Missing gldGA104.bin firmware for Ampere
   - Would need version 455.120_3080 or 455.127 for RTX 3080
2. MODS/MATS require valid VBIOS to initialize GPU memory controller
   - Same FWSEC/DEVINIT chicken-and-egg problem
3. nouveau blacklist in initramfs not effective (needs dracut --force + reboot)

== Conclusion ==
Cannot run GPU memory diagnostics in current state:
  a) Wrong MODS version (367 = Pascal only, need 455 = Ampere)
  b) Even with correct version, MODS needs valid VBIOS to init memory controller
  c) nouveau stuck loaded, blocking MODS from accessing GPU

Memory test must wait until after CH341A VBIOS flash tomorrow.
